---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Speed Building Exercises | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Targeted exercises to build playing speed without sacrificing accuracy. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Speed Building Exercises</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-practice capitalize">practice</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 20 min · Practice Module</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Speed Building Exercises</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Targeted exercises to build playing speed without sacrificing accuracy.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Speed comes from relaxation not force</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Never practice mistakes at speed — slow down first</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Use 1 percent speed increases not 10 percent jumps</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Burst practice: slow slow fast fast slow slow</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Spot practice a 4-note problem rather than whole passage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>The Speed Paradox</h2>
      <p>The fastest path to playing fast is to practice slowly. This sounds contradictory but is completely true. When you practice slowly you build precise neural pathways. When you practice fast before precision is established you reinforce sloppy technique that actually makes you slower long-term. The saying is: slow is smooth and smooth is fast.</p>

      <h2>The 1 Percent Method</h2>
      <p>If you play a passage cleanly at 80 BPM increase to 81 BPM — not 90 not 100 but 81. Spend a full day or two at each new tempo before increasing again. This patient stepwise approach produces real durable speed gains because each increment is fully consolidated before moving forward. Over 6 months 80 BPM naturally becomes 120 BPM.</p>

      <h2>Burst Practice</h2>
      <p>Burst practice alternates between very slow and near-maximum speed. Play the alankar at 60 BPM for 4 repetitions focusing on perfect precision. Then play at your maximum speed for 2 repetitions. Then back to 60 BPM for 4 repetitions. This trains your nervous system to access fast movements while maintaining the precision that slow practice builds.</p>

      <h2>Spot Practice</h2>
      <p>Identify the specific 4 to 6 notes that are slowing you down — it is rarely the whole passage. Isolate just that fragment. Practice only those notes at very slow tempo 50 times in a row with perfect evenness. Then reconnect to the full passage. Targeted spot practice is 5 times more efficient than running the whole piece from start to finish repeatedly.</p>

      <h2>Finger Independence Drills</h2>
      <p>Place your right hand naturally on the keys. Without playing tap fingers independently: index 10 times then middle 10 times then ring 10 times then little finger 10 times. Then pairs: index and middle together middle and ring together ring and little together. This simple finger independence exercise done for 5 minutes before practice directly translates into greater speed and control.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>